com.facebook.util

Class TimeInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.util.TimeInterval

  • public class TimeInterval
extends Object
    Represents Time intervals either as durations or periods and abstracts out operations on time intervals in the System.

    Durations represent a fixed period of time regardless of when they start or end. ie. 1 day will always be 86400 seconds. Instances that represent duration are constructed via withMillis(long).

    Periods represent a period of time but the actual time will depend on when the period starts. For example 1 day will be 23 hours on the first day of DST transition and will be 25 hours on the last day of DST transition. Instances that represent periods are constructed via withTypeAndLength(TimeIntervalType, int).

    The main operations abstracted out are the computation of start of an interval and addition / subtraction of the interval from a time instant.

      • withTypeAndLength

        public static TimeInterval withTypeAndLength(TimeIntervalType type,
                             int length)
        Creates a time interval period based on the supplied type. The actual duration of the period will vary depending on the time instant. The period will take into account DST, varying number of days in a month, leap years, etc.

        Note that if the interval length doesn't divide the maximum value of the interval type equally, the last interval will be of a smaller length than the previous ones. For example if you specify the interval as 40 seconds, the first interval will have the first 40 seconds in a minute and the second interval will have the remaining 20 seconds in the minute.

        Parameters:
        type - the time interval type, cannot be null.
        length - the length of the interval
        Returns:
        the time interval instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if length is less than 1.

      • getIntervalStart

        public org.joda.time.DateTime getIntervalStart(org.joda.time.DateTime instant)
        Gets the start instant of the time interval that will contain the supplied time instant. Note that the time zone of the supplied instant plays a significant role in computation of the interval.
        Parameters:
        instant - the time instant
        Returns:
        the start instant of the time interval that will contain the instant in the time zone of the supplied instant. If the TimeInterval is INFINITE unix epoch for the timezone is returned.
